natspec.author: Victor Marin Felip

buy().details: Attempts to buy the NFT. If enough ETH was sent with the transaction the NFT will be transferred to the sender. Any extra ETH sent will be returned to the sender. The contract selfdestructs after the process. If not enough ETH is sent to buy it at the current price it reverts and nothing happens. Auction needs to be live to work (started and not finished)

constructor.details: The auction needs to be instantiated, then the contract has to be approved at the NFT so it can transfer it to the winner, and then the auction must be started.

params._durationSeconds: auction duration in seconds, msut be 60 seconds at least.
params._nft: address of an ERC721 compatible contract.
params._nftId: Id of the token to be auctioned.
params._reservePrice: reserve price of the auction. Must be less than _startingPrice, can be 0.

destroyAuction().details: Triggers selfdestruct. Only owner can call this function.

getPrice().details: returns the current price based on block.timestamp and the constructor parameters.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

startAuction().details: Starts the auction. The contract needs to be approved first at the NFT.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
